verbose_text: Cocaine (10 muM) significantly inhibited GABA B IPSCs (67.5% +/- 3.0% of control; n = 19; p < 0.0001, paired t test; XREF_FIG) and this was significantly reduced by AM251 (2 muM; 87.2% +/- 4.8% of control, n = 7; p < 0.01, one-way ANOVA, Bonferroni post hoc analysis; XREF_FIG).
